      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/vr-01-rh-index-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index comparison — 5 operating points",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) compared against experimental measurements at five flow-speed operating points. All five predictions yield RH < 1 relative to the predicate device. Mean absolute error is 0.08 RH units across operating points. Uncertainty in experimental measurements is discussed qualitatively in the validation report; variability in blood sample haematocrit (±3%) and pump rotational speed (±15 rpm) contributes to scatter in the experimental baseline. No formal UQ artifact is linked to this result; aleatory uncertainty from biological variability is acknowledged in prose but not quantified through a structured uncertainty propagation exercise.",
      "passFailStatus": "Pass",
      "hasUncertaintyQuantification": "https://uofa.net/synth/uq/uq-01-rh-index-aleatory"
    },
