      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Wall shear stress spatial distribution — PIV benchmark",
      "description": "CFD wall shear stress distribution compared to particle image velocimetry (PIV) data from the FDA benchmark dataset. Spatial agreement within 12% at 90% of measurement locations. Turbulence model sensitivity study conducted with k-omega SST and realizable k-epsilon; differences in peak shear stress predictions are within 8%. Aleatory uncertainty arising from cycle-to-cycle flow variation in the PIV experiment is noted in the discussion section as a source of irreducible scatter but is not linked to any formal uncertainty quantification artifact.",
      "passFailStatus": "Pass"
    },
