    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors are appropriately not assessed per MRL 2 scoping. Validation results demonstrate CFD predictions of relative hemolysis index within 12% of experimental measurements across all five operating points, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion. Uncertainty in biological variability and cycle-to-cycle flow variation is acknowledged in validation narratives; formal UQ artifacts are linked for pressure rise and discretization error factors. The credibility body of evidence is sufficient to support the COU decision for a Class II device at MRL 2.",
